text=:Category: PhonologicalPhenomenaInSpokenLanguages%0a:Essential: {Category.PhonologicalPhenomenaInSpokenLanguages$:essential}%0a:Title: Velarization in Spanish%0a:Author: NickG%0a:Section: C%0a:Completed: 27.03.2021 - 14:40%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210418-225455-380940#%0a* [-18.04.2021 - 15:54-] || TA_lili marked as complete%0a#foxend 210418-225455-380940#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aIn Spanish, particularly Caribbean, the /n/ can become velarized depending on the context.%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIn Spanish (Indo-European), especially Caribbean Spanish, the /n/ is velarized or deleted when it is in the syllable-final or word-final position. When /n/ is deleted, the preceding vowel becomes nasalized.%0aFor example, in word-final positions, the /n/ can become velarized or deleted, so for words like "pan" and "tratan" we see%0a[pan]->[paŋ] or [pã], and likewise [tratan]-> [trataŋ] or [tratã]%0aWhen /n/ appears in syllable-final postions followed by a consonant, it becomes velarized before nasal consonants and dropped before non-nasal consontants. For instance, since the /n/ in "tango" is before a nasal consonant /g/, we get%0a[tango]->[taŋgo]%0aBut since the /n/ in "canto" is before a fricative, we get%0a[kanto]->[kãto]%0a%0aDuring velarization, the back of the tongue raised towards the back of the mouth to maintain the same place of articulation as the following consonant; as seen with [tango]->[taŋgo], this allows the tongue to remain in the same place of articulation for the /ŋ/ and the /g/ sounds. When the /n/ is dropped, the vowel becomes nasalized to mimic the nasal sound of /n/, as seen with [kanto]->[kãto].%0a%0ahttps://dialnet.unirioja.es/descarga/articulo/3269828.pdf%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_lili:)
